+# Security Policy
+
+## Supported Versions
+
+Athanor is in active development. Security fixes are applied to the latest
+release on `main`. Earlier tags are not patched.
+
+| Version          | Supported |
+|------------------|-----------|
+| latest release   | ✅        |
+| older tags       | ❌        |
+
+## Reporting a Vulnerability
+
+Athanor dispatches shell commands and writes to your filesystem through
+Claude Code hooks, skills, and the Codex CLI. If you find a way to make the
+plugin execute unintended commands, exfiltrate session state, or escape the
+documented project-root and file-access boundaries, please report it privately.
+
+**Preferred channel — GitHub private advisory:**
+
+1. Open <https://github.com/WookLabs/athanor/security/advisories/new>
+2. Describe the issue with reproduction steps and a minimal proof-of-concept
+   if possible.
+
+**Fallback channel — public contact-request issue:**
+
+If you cannot access GitHub Security Advisories, open a public issue titled
+`security: contact request` with no details, and a maintainer will reach out
+to establish a private channel.
+
+## Scope
+
+In scope:
+
+- Hook prompts that execute shell commands beyond what the user authorized
+- Skills that read or write files outside the project root
+- Codex CLI dispatch paths that allow argument injection
+- `.athanor/sessions/` or `.athanor/lessons/` artifacts that leak credentials
+
+Out of scope:
+
+- Vulnerabilities in Claude Code itself (report to Anthropic)
+- Vulnerabilities in vendored upstream skills (report to the upstream project
+  listed in `NOTICE.md`)
+- Issues that require already-elevated privileges or physical access
+
+## Response Expectations
+
+This is a single-maintainer project. Acknowledgement: best-effort within
+7 days. Fixes are released as soon as a verified patch is available and
+disclosed alongside the fix in `CHANGELOG.md`.
